{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan Abu Dawud","section":{"15":{"eng-name":"Jihad (Kitab Al-Jihad)","ara-name":"كتاب الجهاد"}},"section_detail":{"15":{"hadithnumber_first":2477,"hadithnumber_last":2787,"arabicnumber_first":2477,"arabicnumber_last":2787}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":2531,"arabicnumber":2531,"text":"حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ السَّلاَمِ بْنُ مُطَهِّرٍ، حَدَّثَنَا جَعْفَرُ بْنُ سُلَيْمَانَ، عَنْ ثَابِتٍ، عَنْ أَنَسٍ، قَالَ ‏:‏ كَانَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم يَغْزُو بِأُمِّ سُلَيْمٍ وَنِسْوَةٍ مِنَ الأَنْصَارِ لِيَسْقِينَ الْمَاءَ وَيُدَاوِينَ الْجَرْحَى ‏.‏","grades":[{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Muhammad Muhyi Al-Din Abdul Hamid","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Shuaib Al Arnaut","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Sahih Muslim (1810)"}],"reference":{"book":15,"hadith":55},"chapter":{"id":34,"ara-name":"باب فِي النِّسَاءِ يَغْزُونَ","eng-name":"Regarding Women Participating In Battle","isFirstHadith":true}}]}